        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let’s get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, crumble in your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> using your hands with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1683882606718-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1683882606718-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1683882606718-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1683882606718-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1683882606718-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>fresh tagliatelle</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>tagliatelle</strong> for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tagliatelle</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1683882613696-x200.jpg",
